Vice President Biden commends the Department of Education for accelerating the distribution of funds from the Recovery Act. Over $2.5 billion will be made available to states in order to support state education budgets and help alleviate fiscal distress. The funds will be used to protect critical jobs and address immediate budget challenges. Vice President Biden applauds Secretary Arne Duncan and his team for their quick action and expresses a commitment to further accelerating the pace of Recovery Act spending.